			],
			"notes": [
				{
					"category": "description",
					"text": "The KVM implementation in the Linux kernel before 2.6.36 does not properly reload the FS and GS segment registers, which allows host OS users to cause a denial of service (host OS crash) via a KVM_RUN ioctl call in conjunction with a modified Local Descriptor Table (LDT).",
					"title": "Vulnerability description"
				},
				{
					"category": "summary",
					"text": "kvm: invalid selector in fs/gs causes kernel panic",
					"title": "Vulnerability summary"
				},
				{
					"category": "general",
					"text": "The CVSS score(s) listed for this vulnerability do not reflect the associated product's status, and are included for informational purposes to better understand the severity of this vulnerability.",
